cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a convolutional neural network architecture for computer vision tasks that encodes rotation equivariance, invariance, and covariance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the reduction in model complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of vector fields and orientation estimation could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the biomedical image segmentation task could suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia).
